âœ… 1. Concept Brief
Class â†’ Blueprint or template for objects

Object â†’ Instance of a class (created using new keyword)

ğŸ–‹ Defining a Class:
java
Copy
Edit
class Student {
    String name;
    int age;

    void displayInfo() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name + ", Age: " + age);
    }
}
ğŸ— Creating an Object:
java
Copy
Edit
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s1 = new Student(); // creating object
        s1.name = "Arhaan";
        s1.age = 21;
        s1.displayInfo();
    }
}
ğŸ”¹ Points to Remember
Class name should start with uppercase (by convention)

Objects store their own data

You can create multiple objects from the same class

ğŸ’» Example: Multiple Objects
java
Copy
Edit
class Car {
    String brand;
    int year;

    void showDetails() {
        System.out.println("Brand: " + brand + ", Year: " + year);
    }
}

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Car car1 = new Car();
        car1.brand = "Tesla";
        car1.year = 2022;

        Car car2 = new Car();
        car2.brand = "BMW";
        car2.year = 2020;

        car1.showDetails();
        car2.showDetails();
    }
}


